            . I am a <rs id="t18270913-124-viclabel708" type="occupation">brush-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-124-victim1290 t18270913-124-viclabel708"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18270913-124-crimeloc709">Spitalfields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-124-crimeloc709" type="placeName" value="Spitalfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-124-crimeloc709" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-124-off705 t18270913-124-crimeloc709"></join>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-124-off707 t18270913-124-crimeloc709"></join> - Mosely was <rs id="t18270913-124-deflabel710" type="occupation">nurse</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-124-defend1288 t18270913-124-deflabel710"></join> in my family, from Easter to July, when she left to go to see her friends - I missed the table-cloth from my bed-room drawer the night she left - a dirty one had been put in its place; next day I found the drawers were stripped of my wife's wearing apparel - the articles stated were gone among others. I got a search-warrant; we found Mosely at work, at a house in Rosemary-lane, where she had gone from my house - the officer searched her, and found some duplicates on her - we went in a coach to her lodgings; we found Sparey sitting there; she said something to her - the officer found a quantity of things there; they have my wife's name on them; my wife died a few days after this, it gave her such a turn when she heard of it - she had been ill for some time. Sparey had called to see Moseley when she was at my house.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Did not you at first find Sparey in the room, and make her tell you where Moseley was? A. Yes; the officer said he had a search-warrant; they told us where most of the things were. I have been robbed by my nephew.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-124-person1294">
                  THOMAS 
                  VANN
               <interp inst="t18270913-124-person1294" type="surname" value="VANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-124-person1294" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-124-person1294" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and took Moseley - as we were in the coach, I saw her put her hand into her pocket; I said, "I must search first." I found some duplicates on her - she then begged Mr. Gardiner's pardon; we found Sparey at the lodgings. I said I had a warrant, and they had better give up the things, which she did - Sparey said, "Moseley had brought them, and told her the sheets would do to shift her bed;" she seemed near her confinement - Moseley said Sparey knew nothing of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-124-person1295">
                  EDWARD 
                  RUBY
               <interp inst="t18270913-124-person1295" type="surname" value="RUBY"></interp>
